parameters: It's an outlet. Not for forks.
There's a thick cable plugged in.
It goes into a hole in the floor, so I can't tell what it goes to.
I don't know what this is for, but should I unplug it anyway?
Takes some effort, but I manage to unplug the cable.
The weight of whatever it's attached to pulls the plug into the floor.
Maybe I shouldn't be messing with everything I find.
There's a rusty liquid left behind where the cable was plugged in.
The section of the carpet looks different.
There's two big indents in the carpet square.
I can't get my fingers underneath to take anything.
Looks like a long way down.
There's a ladder here, but it looks pretty dark down there.
There's also a large metal hook by the top. I better make sure not to clip my chin on that.
Even though the ladder's made from old wood, it's still attached to the wall.
The rope's waiting to get climbed down.
I tied it pretty tightly around the hook, but I'd still be able to take it back in case I need it again.
I untie the \c[4]Rope \c[0]and wrap it back up.
"FATAL ERROR: PLEASE REINSERT BOOT DISK TO FINISH SETUP"
Guess somebody didn't know what they were doing when they were setting this up.
It doesn't like a new computer though. Did someone have to wipe it?
...And there's no way I can take this whole thing with me.
...Nothing's in the disk drive except for a wet spot.
